NHL ALL-STAR WEEKEND
January 19, 1996
Lanny McDonald
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








Q.  When you talk about new facilities going up, is it kind of a trade off that the new buildings get lost, but it is kind of a necessity to have it?

LANNY McDONALD: I think so.  I mean, it always held a special place in everyone's heart when they walked into the Montreal Forum when you considered the amount of Stanley Cups that they have won and the amount of tradition that those walls hold inside of it and the amount of great players that have passed through those doors - when you walk into The Forum, if you aren't up for a game, there is something wrong.


